quran[5]{c,v,t,f}:
2,1,"Alif, Lam, Mim. {1}",footnotes:1:The names of letters of the Arabic alphabet
2,2,"This is the Book of Allah, there is no doubt in it; {1} it is a guidance for the pious, {2}",footnotes:1:This means that while the Book is potentially for all
2,3,"for those who believe in the existence of that which is beyond the reach of perception, {1} who establish Prayer {2} and spend out of what We have provided them, {3}",footnotes:1:This
2,4,"who believe in what has been revealed to you and what was revealed before you, {1} and have firm faith in the Hereafter. {2}",footnotes:1:Belief in the After-life is the sixth and last requirement. The term al-Akhirah embraces a whole set of ideas: (i) that man is not an irresponsible being
2,5,"Such are on true guidance from their Lord; such are the truly successful."
